President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Sim Farar as a member of the United States Advisory Commission on Public Diplomacy. Farar is currently the President of JDF Investments Company and the President and Director of IFC Financial Services. He has previous experience serving as a U.S. Representative to the United Nations and on various advisory boards. Farar holds an A.A. from the College of the Desert and a B.A. from California State University, Northridge.

Additionally, President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Benjamin Cardin and John Cornyn as members of the Board of Trustees of the James Madison Memorial Fellowship Foundation. Cardin and Cornyn will continue their duties as United States Senators while serving on the board. Elizabeth Young McNally has also been appointed as a member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Military Academy. McNally is a management consultant at McKinsey & Co. and a Captain in the U.S. Army Reserves. She has served in various roles during her time in the Army, including as a speechwriter for General David Petraeus during his time in Iraq. McNally is a Rhodes Scholar and Truman Scholar, and she holds a degree from the US Military Academy and a Masters of Philosophy from Oxford University.